OL,7,FOne of the examples given was the Papa
OL,8,FWestray MPA, which is located at the
OL,9,Fnorth end of the island of Papa
OL,10,FWestray in Orkney.
OL,12,FThe group said that despite the area
OL,13,Fbeing designated as an MPA "there are
OL,14,Fstill no restrictions against trawling
OL,15,Fand dredging within or even near the
OL,16,Farea".
OL,18,FThis, the report said, made it "yet
OL,19,Fanother example of a protected area
OL,20,Fthat exists in name and not in
OL,21,Fpractice".
